	<Version rdf:about="tag:bjmns.tumblr.com,2013:bns::1:1:2003-03">
		<owl:sameAs rdf:resource="./1/1/2003-03/"/>
		<owl:sameAs rdf:resource="#bjmns:1:1:2003-03"/>
		<identifier rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#NCName">dimond</identifier>
		<index rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#gYearMonth">2003-03</index>
		<fullTitle xml:lang="en">Tally Marries Dimond</fullTitle>
		<dc:abstract rdf:parseType="Resource">
			<contents rdf:parseType="Literal"><div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" lang="en" xml:lang="en">
  <p>A boy named Tally proposes to and marries his longtime love interest, a girl named Dimond (misspelling intentional).  There existed at least one prior draft with a significantly different plot (as I recall, perhaps there was some competition for Dimond’s hand?), but this has in all likelihood been lost to time and the wastebasket.</p>
  <p>This is quite possibly the first romance story (if you can call it that) I ever wrote, so uh, take from that what you will.</p>
</div></contents>
		</dc:abstract>
